Chairperson of the Pro Makhado Task team Takalani Mukhudi says the shutdown will be intensified in Vuwani in Limpopo. Mukhudi also says they’re demanding the release of the task team member, Arnold Mulaudzi who was arrested on Tuesday night for alleged intimidation and violating the Electoral Act. “We are going to maintain the shutdown – our emotions, morals and everything is very low. They have arrested a person who is an icon of the struggle of the people of Vuwani, we will be actually bussing the people for bail applications if there will be any.” Click on video below:  